Shared types and conventions
- `AppState`: contains typed `Config`, `PgPool`, session store configuration, and shared services.
- `AppError`: one error enum implementing `IntoResponse`; route handlers return `Result<impl IntoResponse, AppError>`.
- `CurrentUser`: extractor that yields authenticated user context, including `user_id`, username, and role.
- `Role`: enum for `User` and `Admin`; avoid stringly typed authorization checks in handlers.
- `Page<T>` or `PaginationParams`: shared pagination DTOs for thread lists, posts, and search results.
- Database rows and web view models stay separate where templates need derived display fields.
- Use repository-style functions in `db::models::*` rather than putting SQL directly in handlers.

Key design decisions
- Use `sqlx::query!` / `query_as!` with offline metadata once the schema stabilizes; this catches schema drift early.
- Run startup in one place: load config, create pool, run pending migrations, build router, serve.
- Keep auth/session concerns in middleware and extractors, not duplicated in handlers.
- Use server-rendered Askama templates everywhere to keep complexity low and match issue scope.
- Support soft deletion for posts with nullable `deleted_at` / `deleted_by`; render tombstones instead of removing rows.
- Model thread state (`pinned`, `locked`) and user state (`is_banned`, `role`) in the database so middleware and handlers share the same source of truth.
- Make flash messages cookie/session-backed and render them in the base template, which aligns with issue #36.
- Build search on PostgreSQL full-text search against denormalized indexed columns; avoid adding external search infrastructure.

Issue dependency order
- Foundation:
  - #1 Cargo project with Axum skeleton
  - #2 environment configuration loader
  - #3 PostgreSQL pool
  - #4 SQLx migrations
  - #5 Askama base layout
  - #6 Tailwind and static assets
  - #7 Dockerfile
- Authentication base:
  - #8 user table
  - #9 password hashing
  - #10 session store
  - #11 registration
  - #12 login/logout
  - #13 auth guard and current-user extractor
- User-facing account features:
  - #14 public profile
  - #15 edit profile
  - #16 change password
- Forum taxonomy and content:
  - #17 category table/model
  - #18 category pages
  - #19 thread/post tables and models
  - #20 markdown and sanitization
  - #21 create thread
  - #22 thread list with pagination
  - #23 thread detail with paginated posts
  - #24 reply to thread
  - #25 edit and soft-delete own post
- Moderation/admin:
  - #26 admin role guard
  - #27 admin category management
  - #28 pin and lock threads
  - #29 admin post deletion
  - #30 user ban
- Discovery and quality:
  - #31 Postgres FTS index
  - #32 search page and handler
  - #33 integration test harness
  - #34 auth integration tests
  - #35 forum integration tests
  - #36 global error pages and flash messages
  - #37 production deployment checklist

Cross-issue implementation notes
- #10 depends on #8 because sessions need a stable user identity model.
- #13 should define the `CurrentUser` contract that later account, thread, and admin handlers all reuse.
- #19 should include foreign keys and useful indexes needed by #22, #23, #28, #29, #30, and #31 so migrations do not churn later.
- #20 should ship before thread/post creation features are considered complete, because content display rules affect storage and rendering choices.
- #26 should be introduced before any admin UI or mutating admin handler is added.
- #31 should be designed with #19 in mind, likely indexing thread title plus post body content through a generated tsvector or trigger-maintained column.
- #33 should establish isolated test database setup and app bootstrap helpers so #34 and #35 are mostly scenario coverage, not infrastructure work.

First-session objective
- This session should only establish repository hygiene and a durable architectural baseline.
- The next implementation session should start with issue #1 and create the crate structure so later issues map cleanly onto the plan above.
